WEBVTT

00:02.290 --> 00:03.790
Dre:
  Nothing makes you feel like

00:03.790 --> 00:05.120
the world is
 full of possibilities

00:05.120 --> 00:06.040
like a brand-new baby.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.330
And you wonder,

00:07.330 --> 00:09.580
what are the paths
 they'll choose?

00:09.580 --> 00:10.920
Will they be a scientist...

00:10.920 --> 00:12.330
or a rock star?

00:12.330 --> 00:13.750
A CEO...

00:13.750 --> 00:15.170
or a farmer?

00:15.170 --> 00:16.790
Will they be a Clippers fan...

00:16.790 --> 00:18.380
or dead to me?

00:18.380 --> 00:21.380
Yep, as parents,
 you can't wait to find out

00:21.380 --> 00:22.830
who your baby's gonna be.

00:22.830 --> 00:25.330
And it all starts
 with the first unknown...

00:25.330 --> 00:27.670
[ Dinging ]
  ...boy or girl?

00:27.670 --> 00:29.250
There's only one thing
more exciting

00:29.250 --> 00:30.920
than learning
the sex of your baby...

00:30.920 --> 00:32.380
I got it! I have it.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.080
[ Chuckles ]
 Uh-huh.

00:34.080 --> 00:36.210
...and that's learning it
 through cake.
 [ Giggles ]

00:36.210 --> 00:37.380
We have a kind of
weird request.

00:37.380 --> 00:39.750
Depending on what is
inside this envelope,

00:39.750 --> 00:41.920
we want you to make
a special cake

00:41.920 --> 00:43.500
that's either blue or pink
on the inside --
 Dre: Come on, Bow.

00:43.500 --> 00:44.750
Get to the point,
all right?

00:44.750 --> 00:45.880
We need a sex cake.

00:45.880 --> 00:47.500
What?
 Uh, no, no,
no, no.

00:47.500 --> 00:48.750
We're not perverts.

00:48.750 --> 00:50.210
We are just having a party

00:50.210 --> 00:52.580
to reveal the gender
of our baby.

00:52.580 --> 00:53.580
Oh! [ Laughs ]

00:53.580 --> 00:54.920
You need
a "Gender reveal cake."

00:54.920 --> 00:56.080
Yes!
 Yes.

00:56.080 --> 00:57.080
Yeah, we do them
all the time.

00:57.080 --> 00:58.420
Oh, my God.
That's so much fun.

00:58.420 --> 00:59.790
Great.
So, you can do this?
 [ Laughing ] Yes.

00:59.790 --> 01:01.620
[ Oh, yeah, we can bake
any kind of cake you want.

01:01.620 --> 01:03.920
Oh!
 Just as long as it's not
for a gay wedding.

01:03.920 --> 01:05.120
I s--

01:06.250 --> 01:09.330
♪♪

01:09.330 --> 01:11.120
I'm taking this.
 Come on, Bow.

01:11.120 --> 01:12.670
All right,
before I do this,

01:12.670 --> 01:14.710
You don't discriminate
against people

01:14.710 --> 01:16.960
based on race, gender,
or sexual orientation,

01:16.960 --> 01:18.000
do you?

01:19.500 --> 01:21.540
Do not like
French-Canadians.

01:21.540 --> 01:22.790
Ah.

01:22.790 --> 01:24.540
I can live with that.
 All right.

01:24.540 --> 01:25.920
We need a sex cake.
 [ Giggles ]

01:30.920 --> 01:31.960
So, babe...

01:31.960 --> 01:33.790
Yep?

01:33.790 --> 01:35.080
...I had the baby dream.

01:35.080 --> 01:36.960
Oh!
 So, remember?

01:36.960 --> 01:38.920
I had the girl dream
before Zoey,

01:38.920 --> 01:40.790
and the boy dream
before Junior,

01:40.790 --> 01:42.080
and then with the twins,

01:42.080 --> 01:44.120
I had the boy dream
and then that lucid nightmare.

01:44.120 --> 01:45.580
Yes. Okay.
What did you dream?

01:45.580 --> 01:47.080
[ Hushed ] A girl.

01:47.880 --> 01:49.460
Oh.
 [ Giggles ]

01:49.460 --> 01:51.000
Really?

01:51.000 --> 01:52.250
See?
I knew it was a girl.

01:52.250 --> 01:53.540
[ Ruby laughs,
smacks Dre ]

01:53.540 --> 01:56.790
A baby girl always steals
her mother's beauty.

01:56.790 --> 01:58.540
And look at your wife.
She's a mess.
 Oh, come on.

01:58.540 --> 02:00.540
Skin all pale,

02:00.540 --> 02:04.790
eyes somehow
both puffy and sunken.

02:04.790 --> 02:05.830
Dre: Wow, I see that.

02:05.830 --> 02:07.750
Mm-hmm.
 Mm-hmm.

02:07.750 --> 02:09.210
Thank you, Ruby.

02:09.210 --> 02:10.539
But I'm not gonna let you
get to me.

02:10.539 --> 02:14.170
I'm just happy
that I get to name our baby.

02:14.170 --> 02:15.380
If it's a girl...
 Mm-hmm.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.250
...and if it's a boy,
I get to name him.

02:17.250 --> 02:18.750
Mm-hmm.
  That was the deal.

02:18.750 --> 02:21.250
So, I get to name
our baby girl.

02:21.250 --> 02:24.000
And from the looks of you,
she's gonna be very healthy.

02:24.000 --> 02:25.790
She might even
be immortal --

02:25.790 --> 02:28.380
an immortal supermodel.

02:28.380 --> 02:29.880
[ Laughs ] Yeah.

02:29.880 --> 02:31.500
♪♪

02:31.500 --> 02:32.460
[ Ringtone chimes ]

02:32.460 --> 02:33.880
Ugh, Doug's asking me

02:33.880 --> 02:35.120
about Valentine's Day
again.

02:35.120 --> 02:36.670
[ Scoffs ] Delete.

02:36.670 --> 02:38.330
Shelly, is it just me,

02:38.330 --> 02:40.960
or are guys at school
super thirsty this year?

02:40.960 --> 02:43.000
Oh, senior guys
are the worst.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.540
Let's just skip
Valentine's Day.

02:44.540 --> 02:46.040
That's an awesome plan.

02:46.040 --> 02:48.620
Let's do this
Ladies' Valentine's Day.

02:48.620 --> 02:52.540
You and me -- well, us.
No new friends, am I right?

02:52.540 --> 02:55.710
Sorry, little mama,
you're a little too young.

02:55.710 --> 02:57.290
And completely creepy.

02:57.290 --> 02:59.580
Like, when did you even
get into my room?

02:59.580 --> 03:02.080
I'm positive
that door was locked.

03:02.080 --> 03:03.500
Well, good day,

03:03.500 --> 03:05.540
and thank you
for the feedback.

03:05.540 --> 03:08.080
I'll keep the 14th open
just in case.

03:08.080 --> 03:09.500
Yeah.

03:09.500 --> 03:10.880
[ Door closes ]

03:10.880 --> 03:14.290
World record attempt --
take nine.

03:14.290 --> 03:16.120
[ Inhales, exhales ]

03:19.960 --> 03:21.290
Boom. Did you get that?

03:21.290 --> 03:23.500
Uh, no.

03:23.500 --> 03:25.380
Shelly:
I mean, it's really cute.
 Jack: Oh, hey!

03:25.380 --> 03:26.920
Shelly! Hugs?

03:26.920 --> 03:29.120
Aww,
could you get any cuter?

03:29.120 --> 03:30.380
Nope.

03:30.380 --> 03:32.330
What are you up to?
 You know, just chilling.

03:32.330 --> 03:33.540
What's up, Junior?

03:33.540 --> 03:35.210
Pretty big day.

03:35.210 --> 03:37.170
Trying to set the world record
on Sir Rubik's.

03:37.170 --> 03:39.000
Oh, he's --
He's just chilling, too.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.210
Rubik's Cube?
You good at this?

03:41.210 --> 03:42.500
I'm all right.

03:43.330 --> 03:45.000
I bet you're better
than all right.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.580
♪♪

03:47.580 --> 03:49.380
I'll see you later.

03:49.380 --> 03:51.290
Y-- You know what that was,
right?

03:51.290 --> 03:52.500
You know I don't.

03:52.500 --> 03:53.580
She's feeling you.

03:53.580 --> 03:55.080
[ High-pitched ] What?

03:55.080 --> 03:57.210
Pretty sure she was just
being polite,

03:57.210 --> 03:59.120
even though I specifically
told her not to.

03:59.120 --> 04:00.830
But, trust me,
I know Shelly,

04:00.830 --> 04:02.120
and you're not
her type.

04:02.120 --> 04:03.500
I'm still not convinced

04:03.500 --> 04:06.080
you're not gonna get
pig's blood thrown
on you at prom.

04:06.080 --> 04:07.750
Like they'd do that
to me again.

04:07.750 --> 04:08.960
[ Ringtone chimes ]

04:08.960 --> 04:10.460
Hey,
Shelly just texted you.

04:10.460 --> 04:12.500
Shelly:
 Good luck on that world record.

04:12.500 --> 04:14.750
Check out this
 Rubik's Cube tutorial.

04:14.750 --> 04:15.670
Winky-kiss emoji."

04:15.670 --> 04:17.250
Wow.

04:17.250 --> 04:19.329
She is really polite.

04:19.329 --> 04:21.709
♪♪

04:21.709 --> 04:23.880
Stevens: You're looking
a little off today, Dre.

04:23.880 --> 04:25.170
You okay?

04:25.170 --> 04:26.170
You got the 'itis?

04:26.170 --> 04:27.750
No.

04:27.750 --> 04:29.460
And never say that again.

04:29.460 --> 04:31.040
Bow thinks that
we're gonna have a girl,

04:31.040 --> 04:32.290
so I'm a little
bummed out.

04:32.290 --> 04:33.960
Ohh.
 Uh, yeah,
of course you are,

04:33.960 --> 04:35.620
'cause girls
are the worst.
 Mm-hmm.

04:35.620 --> 04:37.960
Everything's "No, Josh."
"Leave me alone, Josh."

04:37.960 --> 04:39.500
"We're cousins, Josh."
Or --
 Yeah, or like,

04:39.500 --> 04:40.750
"How did you get in here,
Josh?"

04:40.750 --> 04:42.710
Or "What is that you're
holding in your hand, Josh?"

04:42.710 --> 04:44.920
Or like, "I have
GPS on my phone, Josh."
 [ Chuckles ] Okay.

04:44.920 --> 04:46.460
I'm right there with you,
brother.
 Cool.

04:46.460 --> 04:48.420
Look, the proof
that boys are better

04:48.420 --> 04:50.000
is sitting right here.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.790
Do you see a woman
in this room?

04:51.790 --> 04:52.790
[ Chuckling ]
 Not a one.

04:52.790 --> 04:54.830
Again...

04:54.830 --> 04:56.750
I'm a corporate evaluator
here to judge productivity

04:56.750 --> 04:59.880
and ultimately whether or not
you should work here.

04:59.880 --> 05:01.420
[ Mocking ]
Merr-merr-merr corporate.

05:01.420 --> 05:02.710
[ Laughter ]

05:02.710 --> 05:03.670
Oh, let me just...

05:03.670 --> 05:05.330
[ Normal voice ] What, uh --
What are you --

05:05.330 --> 05:06.420
What are you
writing down there?

05:06.420 --> 05:08.620
What do you think
I'm writing down?

05:08.620 --> 05:09.830
Anyone else?

05:09.830 --> 05:11.210
Not me.
[ Laughs nervously ]

05:11.210 --> 05:13.380
I think you're intelligent,
competent,

05:13.380 --> 05:17.290
and I am completely
unattracted to you.
 Dre: Mm.

05:17.290 --> 05:19.380
But you can still
get it.
 Oh, man.

05:19.380 --> 05:20.040
What's wrong with me?

05:20.040 --> 05:21.420
What's wrong with me?
 Rachel: [ Clears throat ]

05:21.420 --> 05:23.710
I -- I -- I don't know.
 W-- W-- Why do I think
like that?

05:23.710 --> 05:24.830
Rachel:
Dre, as you can see,

05:24.830 --> 05:27.170
men are just monsters,
you know?

05:27.170 --> 05:28.620
And let's face it,

05:28.620 --> 05:30.290
it's your daughters
that are gonna take care of you

05:30.290 --> 05:31.290
when you're old.

05:31.290 --> 05:32.920
Oh, my God.

05:32.920 --> 05:34.790
You're right.

05:34.790 --> 05:36.960
Zoey's gonna
take care of me.

05:36.960 --> 05:38.670
And when it's time
for you to go,

05:38.670 --> 05:40.500
Diane will put an air bubble
in your I.V.

05:40.500 --> 05:42.210
Hey.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa --

05:42.210 --> 05:44.750
All right, look,
Diane is a sweet, good girl.

05:44.750 --> 05:46.120
And if I'm ever
in a bar fight,

05:46.120 --> 05:47.880
there's no one
I'd rather have than her.

05:47.880 --> 05:48.920
Yeah, that's true.

05:48.920 --> 05:50.420
She...she will get down
with you.

05:50.420 --> 05:51.790
Stevens: Okay, stop it.

05:51.790 --> 05:53.620
Your sons
are your pride and joy.

05:53.620 --> 05:54.830
They carry you're name.

05:54.830 --> 05:56.000
They're
your little warriors.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.000
Thanks, Papa.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.210
And I'm sure
that if my brothers

05:58.210 --> 05:59.790
were not stuck in that
Ecuadorian embassy in London,

05:59.790 --> 06:00.880
they would also agree.

06:00.880 --> 06:02.210
Mm. Bingo.

06:02.210 --> 06:03.670
They're in
a lot of trouble.
 [ Chuckles ]

06:03.670 --> 06:05.580
Dre: After listening
 to these idiots,

06:05.580 --> 06:07.540
maybe having a girl
 was the way to go.

06:07.540 --> 06:10.290
Jack: Look in the mirror --
Look deep.

06:10.290 --> 06:11.460
What do you see?

06:11.460 --> 06:13.080
A level 7 wizard.

06:13.080 --> 06:14.500
[ Sighs ] Look deeper.

06:14.500 --> 06:15.580
No way I'm level 8!

06:15.580 --> 06:17.540
I can't control fire.

06:17.540 --> 06:20.580
Junior, no one around here
wants me to tell you this,

06:20.580 --> 06:23.250
but you're really starting
to become something.

06:23.250 --> 06:26.420
I am?
 Nice face,
smooth skin --

06:26.420 --> 06:28.000
really starting
to fill out that frame.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.120
I have thought about
wearing a tank top.

06:30.120 --> 06:31.580
I've thought about you
wearing a tank top!

06:31.580 --> 06:34.250
Bruh, Shelly's into you.

06:34.250 --> 06:35.380
You've just got
to talk to her.

06:35.380 --> 06:36.920
I can't. I --

06:36.920 --> 06:39.580
But that guy can --
the one in the mirror.

06:39.580 --> 06:40.920
Can you do that?

06:41.960 --> 06:44.120
I think I can.

06:44.120 --> 06:45.670
No.

06:45.670 --> 06:48.210
I think he can.

06:48.210 --> 06:50.170
[ Indistinct conversation ]

06:50.170 --> 06:52.040
What's up, girl?

06:52.040 --> 06:53.460
You just gonna keep
walking by my room

06:53.460 --> 06:55.040
looking all good?

06:55.040 --> 06:57.210
[ Chuckles ]
 Uh, what's up, Junior?

06:57.210 --> 06:59.790
Just counting my birthday money,
you know.

06:59.790 --> 07:01.710
What is happening
right now?

07:01.710 --> 07:03.670
[ Inhales sharply ]
What you talking about, Zoey?

07:03.670 --> 07:05.540
It's getting hot in here,
am I right?

07:05.540 --> 07:06.620
Oh, my G-- Mom!

07:08.080 --> 07:09.250
Is that a shark
on your tank top?

07:09.250 --> 07:11.920
Great white.
Got hella teeth.

07:11.920 --> 07:14.120
They got these down at
the Long Beach Aquarium.

07:14.120 --> 07:15.920
You know,
if you ever want to roll,

07:15.920 --> 07:17.500
my family's got a membership
down there,

07:17.500 --> 07:18.540
which includes a guest,

07:18.540 --> 07:20.080
so that's nothing.

07:20.080 --> 07:22.420
Shelly, I am so sorry.
Come on.

07:22.420 --> 07:24.210
Yeah, Shelly, come on.

07:24.210 --> 07:26.000
"Boy, bye." Am I right?

07:26.000 --> 07:28.120
Yeah.

07:28.120 --> 07:29.580
Shark tank top?

07:31.920 --> 07:34.750
So I was 100% Team Girl now.

07:34.750 --> 07:36.330
I'd ditched my dreams
 of having a boy,

07:36.330 --> 07:37.960
like Kevin Durant
 ditched the Thunder.

07:37.960 --> 07:39.210
Team Girl! Mm.

07:39.210 --> 07:41.500
Ruby: All right, everybody,
gather around!

07:41.500 --> 07:43.880
Let's find out
the gender of this baby

07:43.880 --> 07:47.040
before Rainbow's puffy ankles
require her to lie down.

07:47.040 --> 07:49.290
Come on. [ Laughs ]
 Dre: Hey, baby.

07:49.290 --> 07:50.380
Yes?
 You ready for this?

07:50.380 --> 07:51.330
Oh, I'm very ready.
I'm so excited!

07:51.330 --> 07:52.580
Okay, ready?

07:52.580 --> 07:53.460
You ready?
 Diane: Mm-hmm.

07:53.460 --> 07:56.420
All: Three, two, one...

07:57.290 --> 07:58.790
[ All cheering ]

07:58.790 --> 08:01.080
Ruby: [ Laughs ]

08:01.080 --> 08:02.670
Blue?

08:02.670 --> 08:03.540
Wha-- Uh--

08:03.540 --> 08:05.330
Blue.
 Blue?

08:05.330 --> 08:06.880
Blue!
 Yeah...

08:06.880 --> 08:08.290
It's a boy!

08:08.290 --> 08:10.380
Yes! Yes!!
 Okay.

08:10.380 --> 08:13.170
[ Laughs ]
 Dre, I thought you were
"100% Team Girl."

08:13.170 --> 08:15.290
Why would I want that,
huh?

08:15.290 --> 08:16.710
Oh!
Now I get to finally have

08:16.710 --> 08:18.540
the son I always wanted
but never got!

08:18.540 --> 08:20.460
Yes!

08:20.460 --> 08:22.080
Oh, you are the one, son.

08:22.080 --> 08:23.580
[ Laughs ]
 You are the one!

08:24.710 --> 08:25.960
DeVonté.

08:25.960 --> 08:28.710
Yeah! Yes!
 DeVonté?

08:28.710 --> 08:30.000
♪ Hoo, yeah ♪
 DeVonté?

08:34.080 --> 08:36.120
You're not serious

08:36.120 --> 08:38.039
about naming our kid DeVonté,
are you?

08:38.039 --> 08:40.169
Yes.
 No.

08:40.169 --> 08:41.830
What exactly is your problem
with that name?

08:41.830 --> 08:43.960
It's unconventional, Dre.

08:43.960 --> 08:46.750
I grew up as "Rainbow,"
okay?

08:46.750 --> 08:48.460
"Rainbow."
That was not easy.

08:48.460 --> 08:49.580
Yeah,
that's because Rainbow

08:49.580 --> 08:51.000
is the name
that white people...

08:51.000 --> 08:52.290
[ Groans ]
 ...give
cocker spaniels.

08:52.290 --> 08:54.790
Stop it!
 DeVonté
is a great name.

08:54.790 --> 08:56.710
It has
cultural significance!

08:56.710 --> 08:58.790
"DeVonté" is the name

08:58.790 --> 09:01.750
of the least important member
of Jodeci.
 No!

09:01.750 --> 09:03.830
The least important
member of Jodeci

09:03.830 --> 09:05.120
was Mr. Dalvin...
 No.

09:05.120 --> 09:06.960
...and you know that.
 No, I don't!

09:06.960 --> 09:09.210
There's a different reason

09:09.210 --> 09:10.960
that you don't like
the name "DeVonté."

09:10.960 --> 09:11.880
What?

09:11.880 --> 09:13.120
Yep.

09:13.120 --> 09:14.460
It's because
it's too black.

09:14.460 --> 09:16.580
Thank you, Mama.
 Mm-hmm.

09:16.580 --> 09:17.880
And she's right.

09:17.880 --> 09:20.080
Ah. Thank you, Mama.

09:20.080 --> 09:21.420
Oh, my God.

09:21.420 --> 09:22.710
That doesn't even sound right
coming out of your mouth.

09:22.710 --> 09:23.920
Well, I felt it.
 Listen, listen, listen.

09:23.920 --> 09:26.040
Those made-up names
are a travesty.

09:26.040 --> 09:28.540
You need to give that boy
a strong name --

09:28.540 --> 09:30.540
something powerful,
biblical.

09:30.540 --> 09:32.710
Something that won't
give away the fact
that he's black

09:32.710 --> 09:34.540
until you hear him
talking on the phone.

09:34.540 --> 09:36.120
Now, you know we can tell
if somebody's black

09:36.120 --> 09:37.460
on the phone.

09:37.460 --> 09:38.670
Yeah, we can always tell.
 You can tell.

09:38.670 --> 09:39.830
That's true. Mm-hmm.
 How about "Michael,"

09:39.830 --> 09:41.040
or "Christopher."

09:41.040 --> 09:43.540
Hell, I'd even take
a "Dustin."

09:43.540 --> 09:45.830
Just nothing too ghetto,
y'all.

09:45.830 --> 09:47.920
Okay, well,
I want a strong, Black name.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.420
Oh, boy.

09:49.420 --> 09:51.750
Okay, because we've given
our kids White names,

09:51.750 --> 09:54.460
and they've all ended up
"Black-ish."
 What?

09:54.460 --> 09:56.380
Dre --
 I just want at least
one of my kids

09:56.380 --> 09:57.290
to end up being Black,

09:57.290 --> 09:58.880
so I could love it.
 Hey --

09:58.880 --> 09:59.880
[ Stammers ]

09:59.880 --> 10:01.000
What?
 Zoey: Oh.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.580
We were just
coming downstairs

10:02.580 --> 10:04.170
to see if there
was any cake left.

10:04.170 --> 10:07.290
But I guess we'll just
eat our sadness instead.

10:07.290 --> 10:08.460
[ Clears throat ]

10:08.460 --> 10:10.120
Hi, everybody.

10:10.120 --> 10:12.580
My wife's dumb dream
was wrong.

10:12.580 --> 10:14.080
We are having a boy.

10:14.080 --> 10:16.670
-Oh!
-Congratulations!

10:16.670 --> 10:18.580
[ Laughs ]
 Yeah, so smoke up

10:18.580 --> 10:21.380
in honor of my future son,
DeVonté.

10:21.380 --> 10:22.880
Josh: Oh, boy.
 Stevens: Oh.

10:22.880 --> 10:24.580
So you're doing that,
huh?

10:24.580 --> 10:25.830
What?
 Wow.

10:25.830 --> 10:27.080
You're not gonna
even go, like,

10:27.080 --> 10:29.000
"Vernon" or "Marcus"
or "Leon"?

10:29.000 --> 10:30.210
Just going straight to

10:30.210 --> 10:32.620
NFL free safety Black-name
territory, huh?

10:32.620 --> 10:33.920
Charlie:
I don't know about that name.

10:33.920 --> 10:35.080
If I'm on a plane
and I hear

10:35.080 --> 10:36.380
"Welcome aboard,

10:36.380 --> 10:38.250
I'm your captain
DeVonté Johnson,"

10:38.250 --> 10:39.710
I'm no longer aboard.

10:39.710 --> 10:41.120
Word?
 Word.

10:41.120 --> 10:43.500
Dre, "DeVonté" sounds like
two names played chicken

10:43.500 --> 10:44.920
and nobody won.

10:44.920 --> 10:46.380
Stevens: Yeah, you guys have
a lot of names like that,

10:46.380 --> 10:47.710
like, uh, "Shaniqua."

10:47.710 --> 10:49.170
"Montell."
 "D'Brickashaw."

10:49.170 --> 10:50.620
"NyQuil."

10:50.620 --> 10:53.380
Do you hear how racist
you both sound?

10:53.380 --> 10:54.670
Those are real names.
 I was just making a point.

10:54.670 --> 10:56.000
Facts.
 Well, growing up,

10:56.000 --> 10:58.420
I did have a friend
by the name of "NyQuil."

10:58.420 --> 11:00.420
He was always
sniffing and sneezing,

11:00.420 --> 11:03.040
coughing, stuffy-headed --
 Charlie, you did not have
a friend named that.

11:03.040 --> 11:05.620
Yeah. Sometimes I lie.

11:05.620 --> 11:06.830
Seriously, guys,
you don't get it, do you?

11:06.830 --> 11:08.420
You remember "Roots"?

11:08.420 --> 11:09.670
Remember? [ Laughs ]

11:09.670 --> 11:11.250
I'm proud to say
I never saw it.

11:11.250 --> 11:12.380
Charlie,
you saw "Roots," right?

11:12.380 --> 11:13.710
You know I did,
Black man.

11:13.710 --> 11:15.170
Ah, no you didn't.

11:15.170 --> 11:16.880
I did not, Black man.
 Okay, look.

11:16.880 --> 11:19.250
There's a scene in the movie
where Kunta Kinte --

11:19.250 --> 11:21.170
Oh, what is that?
I don't know what that is.

11:22.620 --> 11:23.620
LeVar Burton?

11:23.620 --> 11:24.830
Oh, "Reading Rainbow."

11:24.830 --> 11:26.670
The Black dude
from "Star Trek."
 Yeah.

11:26.670 --> 11:28.920
Okay, look, Levar Burton
is forced to give up

11:28.920 --> 11:30.580
his African name

11:30.580 --> 11:33.000
and take
the slave name "Toby."

11:33.000 --> 11:34.420
All right, Black people
were brought over here,

11:34.420 --> 11:35.750
and when we were,

11:35.750 --> 11:37.210
we were robbed
of our African names.

11:37.210 --> 11:39.380
Hmm.
 So when
we got the chance

11:39.380 --> 11:41.080
to take control
of our destiny

11:41.080 --> 11:44.420
we started by taking control
of our names.

11:44.420 --> 11:46.710
Yes, sir.
 The Black Muslims
did it first --

11:46.710 --> 11:49.210
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar,
Muhammad Ali.

11:49.210 --> 11:50.880
Yes, sir.
 Then there was
the Black nationalists

11:50.880 --> 11:52.080
and Afrocentrists --

11:52.080 --> 11:54.420
Amiri Baraka, Kwame Ture.

11:54.420 --> 11:56.250
Mm.
 Over the years,

11:56.250 --> 11:57.830
we, uh,
got a little creative,

11:57.830 --> 12:02.330
and you got the names
Michel'le and God Shammgod.

12:02.330 --> 12:03.500
But...
 That's not real.

12:03.500 --> 12:04.830
...we are also the people

12:04.830 --> 12:07.040
that gave you
jazz and hip-hop,

12:07.040 --> 12:08.080
so back off.

12:08.080 --> 12:09.500
Charlie: He's right.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.380
We have nothing
to be ashamed of.

12:11.380 --> 12:13.500
Mnh-mnh.
 And for now on,

12:13.500 --> 12:16.080
you will know me
by my true name --

12:16.080 --> 12:19.790
King Charlemagne
Fatback Telphy the Third.

12:19.790 --> 12:21.380
Oh, okay.

12:23.080 --> 12:24.330
Hey, Shelly.

12:24.330 --> 12:26.460
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry

12:26.460 --> 12:28.290
for the way
I acted yesterday.

12:28.290 --> 12:30.880
You're really beautiful and cool
and I'm not,

12:30.880 --> 12:32.120
but I listened
to my little brother,

12:32.120 --> 12:33.670
and I shouldn't have,

12:33.670 --> 12:34.920
because I've never seen him
with a girl,

12:34.920 --> 12:36.500
and I'm pretty sure
he sill wears Pull-ups.

12:36.500 --> 12:39.620
Oh, uh, those are just
disposable sleep shorts.

12:39.620 --> 12:43.000
Anyway, like I was saying,
I'm sorry.

12:43.000 --> 12:44.960
Now you can go back
to ignoring me.

12:44.960 --> 12:46.000
Wait a second.

12:48.250 --> 12:50.460
What if I don't
want to ignore you?

12:50.460 --> 12:52.460
What?! Shelly, ew!

12:52.460 --> 12:54.750
And, Junior,
don't you have to go text

12:54.750 --> 12:57.500
your super-serious,
super-annoying girlfriend?

12:57.500 --> 12:58.880
Girlfriend?

12:58.880 --> 13:00.040
Actually, we've talked,

13:00.040 --> 13:01.620
and Megan's
not into the words

13:01.620 --> 13:03.250
"Girlfriend"
or "Boyfriend."

13:03.250 --> 13:05.040
We don't believe in labels
and ownership.

13:05.040 --> 13:06.540
She's really cool.

13:06.540 --> 13:08.750
She's sounds cool.

13:08.750 --> 13:10.750
That's like
sophomore-year-of-college stuff.

13:10.750 --> 13:13.540
Or something
two weirdos would do.

13:13.540 --> 13:15.960
Anyway,
I'm gonna go grab a soda.
 Wait!

13:15.960 --> 13:17.580
Can I get one of those?

13:17.580 --> 13:19.420
I think we only have one.

13:19.420 --> 13:21.620
Oh, uh, um --
Mom just bought some more.

13:21.620 --> 13:23.080
[ Hushed ]
This is the last time

13:23.080 --> 13:24.920
I'm going to save you.

13:24.920 --> 13:26.790
Come on, Shelly.
I'll get us some soda.

13:26.790 --> 13:27.830
That's okay.

13:27.830 --> 13:29.540
Junior's got it.

13:29.540 --> 13:32.330
♪♪

13:33.460 --> 13:34.380
Let's go.

13:36.290 --> 13:38.380
I can't believe this.

13:38.380 --> 13:39.540
I can't believe it,
either.

13:39.540 --> 13:41.880
How are you here?

13:41.880 --> 13:44.920
Guess it's time for
a little sisters-only
Valentine's Day.

13:44.920 --> 13:46.290
Come here, sister!

13:46.290 --> 13:47.580
Ahh.

13:47.580 --> 13:49.120
[ Sniffs ]

13:49.120 --> 13:51.250
Is this
what hugging feels like?

13:51.250 --> 13:52.420
It's really nice.

13:52.420 --> 13:54.880
Why are you petting me?

13:54.880 --> 13:57.380
Working with racists
 finally had paid off,

13:57.380 --> 13:59.000
because I knew,
 more than ever,

13:59.000 --> 14:01.710
I had to defend my choice
 to give my son a Black name.

14:01.710 --> 14:05.250
Yeah, you don't want
to name our son DeVonté,

14:05.250 --> 14:07.620
because you're a racist.
 Dre --

14:07.620 --> 14:09.540
Just like all the fools at work,
Donald Sterling,

14:09.540 --> 14:11.250
and everyone at Ruth's Chris

14:11.250 --> 14:13.710
who assumes
I like my steaks well done.

14:13.710 --> 14:15.170
You do like your steaks
well done.

14:15.170 --> 14:16.830
That doesn't mean
it's not racist.
 Okay.

14:16.830 --> 14:18.210
Dre,
can we just be honest here?
 Okay.

14:18.210 --> 14:21.040
There's some names
that handcuff you.

14:21.040 --> 14:23.920
There's never gonna be
a President DeVonté Johnson.

14:23.920 --> 14:25.920
There was
a President Barack Obama.

14:25.920 --> 14:28.170
People are more accepting
of African names, Dre.

14:28.170 --> 14:29.290
Oh.
 Everybody knows that.

14:29.290 --> 14:30.290
They sound dignified.

14:30.290 --> 14:31.670
"Chiwetel Ejiofor"?

14:31.670 --> 14:32.880
Yep.
 Ugh.

14:32.880 --> 14:34.250
You're so sure

14:34.250 --> 14:36.540
that America's gonna have
a problem with DeVonté?

14:36.540 --> 14:38.120
Mm-hmm.
 Yeah, well,
I'm gonna get me a drink.

14:38.120 --> 14:39.620
Okay.

14:39.620 --> 14:43.710
Uh, could I have
a large Americano, please?

14:43.710 --> 14:45.460
Can I get a name
for that order?
 Sure you can.

14:45.460 --> 14:46.620
It's...

14:46.620 --> 14:47.500
DeVonté.

14:47.500 --> 14:49.330
Oh, my --

14:49.330 --> 14:50.580
Thanks, DeVonté.
Your order will be right up.

14:50.580 --> 14:53.540
Oh, boy.
 Thank you, Scarlett.

14:53.540 --> 14:55.000
Very nice --
Very nice, Dre.
 Yes, it is.

14:55.000 --> 14:57.830
You know, I feel
I say this a lot...
 Mm-hmm.

14:57.830 --> 14:59.330
You're dead wrong.

14:59.330 --> 15:00.580
Okay.
 Okay?

15:00.580 --> 15:02.750
"Baby boy DeVonté"
is gonna be just fine.

15:02.750 --> 15:04.380
Dre, can you look at this
for me?
 Sure.

15:04.380 --> 15:05.250
Okay.

15:05.250 --> 15:07.500
I put
two identical résumés

15:07.500 --> 15:09.880
on this hiring website.
 Mm-hmm.

15:09.880 --> 15:13.170
"Michael Johnson"
got numerous responses.

15:13.170 --> 15:14.960
Mm-hmm.
 "DeVonté Johnson" --

15:14.960 --> 15:18.750
one ad for a bail bonds.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.170
I feel sad for you...

15:20.170 --> 15:21.830
Oh, my God.

15:21.830 --> 15:24.670
...that your mind isn't
as open as our barista's.

15:24.670 --> 15:26.880
Okay.
 Man:
I got a Vente for Dave?

15:26.880 --> 15:29.330
Dave, Vente?

15:29.330 --> 15:32.000
Oh,
it's a tea for Devon.

15:32.000 --> 15:33.250
Uh --

15:33.250 --> 15:34.670
Devon tea?

15:34.670 --> 15:35.750
Devon's tea?

15:35.750 --> 15:36.880
[ Sighs ]

15:36.880 --> 15:38.460
Got a hot tea for Devon.

15:38.460 --> 15:39.790
Okay, look here, homey,
let's stop playing games.

15:39.790 --> 15:41.750
You know this is mine.

15:41.750 --> 15:43.330
All right.
You ain't got no Black friends?

15:43.330 --> 15:45.330
DeVonté. Jodeci.
Look it up.

15:45.330 --> 15:48.120
And that was the last straw.

15:48.120 --> 15:49.620
The dreams of DeVonté

15:49.620 --> 15:52.540
were dashed by a barista
 named Augustus.

15:57.000 --> 15:58.580
French bread pizza?
[ Chuckles ]

15:58.580 --> 16:00.830
I'm not allowed
to use the big oven.

16:00.830 --> 16:02.670
You don't need to know
the backstory,

16:02.670 --> 16:04.880
but be assured,
it is justified.

16:04.880 --> 16:06.170
[ Doorbell chimes ]

16:06.170 --> 16:09.210
Oh! Help yourself
to some Coke or Diet Coke.

16:09.210 --> 16:10.330
I put them
in the fancy pitchers,

16:10.330 --> 16:11.790
and now I don't know
which is which.

16:11.790 --> 16:13.380
Zoey:
[ Exhales sharply ]

16:13.380 --> 16:15.670
Why is she into him?

16:15.670 --> 16:16.960
[ Door opens ]
 He's attractive.

16:16.960 --> 16:18.380
He's coming into his body.

16:18.380 --> 16:21.210
Please tell me
you didn't tell him that.

16:21.210 --> 16:23.040
He deserves to know.
 [ Door closes ]

16:26.580 --> 16:28.540
It's not every day
that I get to introduce

16:28.540 --> 16:30.790
two amazing women
to each other.

16:30.790 --> 16:32.710
Megan, this is Shelly.

16:32.710 --> 16:34.000
Shelly, Megan.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.830
What is happening here?

16:35.830 --> 16:38.620
You invited your girlfriend
to our Valentine's Day?

16:38.620 --> 16:41.580
Yeah, because you said
you thought she sounded cool.

16:41.580 --> 16:43.210
And, besides,
she's not my girlfriend.

16:43.210 --> 16:44.210
I'm not?

16:44.210 --> 16:45.540
Yeah...

16:45.540 --> 16:47.290
because you said you don't
believe in ownership.

16:47.290 --> 16:49.170
I only said that
so you'd step up.

16:49.170 --> 16:51.540
Wait, wait.
I'm being honest.

16:51.540 --> 16:53.120
I like you,
and I also like you,

16:53.120 --> 16:54.420
and I don't want
to hide that.

16:54.420 --> 16:56.380
Oh,
so you're a player.
 No.

16:56.380 --> 16:58.420
I'm an honest man
standing in front of you

16:58.420 --> 17:00.290
asking you both
to go out with me.

17:00.290 --> 17:03.000
Separately.
Except for tonight.

17:03.000 --> 17:04.420
I made pizza for three.

17:04.420 --> 17:06.420
Yeah, I'm out.
 Me, too.

17:06.420 --> 17:07.829
Do you need a ride?
 Sure.

17:07.829 --> 17:09.250
Wait.
 [ Scoffs ]

17:09.250 --> 17:10.710
Where are you going?

17:10.710 --> 17:12.670
I-- I'm coming into my body.

17:12.670 --> 17:13.790
[ Door slams ]

17:13.790 --> 17:15.170
You're right.

17:15.170 --> 17:17.380
He was not ready
to hear that.

17:17.380 --> 17:18.880
[ Whimpers ]

17:21.000 --> 17:23.210
Anything interesting?

17:23.210 --> 17:25.170
Uh, nope.

17:25.170 --> 17:26.579
The only thing
I came up with

17:26.579 --> 17:29.750
is "Matthew," "Daniel,"
and "Kevin."

17:29.750 --> 17:31.880
Oh. Those are nice.

17:31.880 --> 17:34.500
Yeah, but they don't
mean anything to me, babe.

17:34.500 --> 17:36.380
[ Sighs ]
 I like
the name DeVonté.

17:36.380 --> 17:39.830
Dre,
this is our baby.
 Yes.

17:39.830 --> 17:41.830
You don't choose a name
to prove a point, Dre.

17:41.830 --> 17:43.330
But, babe,
I'm not trying to.

17:43.330 --> 17:46.540
Look, I grew up
with the Ledariuses,

17:46.540 --> 17:49.290
the JaMarcuses,
and the DeQuans.
 [ Sighs ]

17:49.290 --> 17:51.620
Hey, look, those names
reflect who we are.

17:51.620 --> 17:54.330
And the only reason
we're not naming our son DeVonté

17:54.330 --> 17:57.830
is so people won't
know right away
that he's Black.

17:57.830 --> 18:00.380
I hate the fact
that when something is Black,

18:00.380 --> 18:02.790
the world sees it
as bad.

18:02.790 --> 18:04.960
Me, too.

18:04.960 --> 18:06.620
So, if we're gonna
raise our baby

18:06.620 --> 18:08.620
to be proud of who he is,

18:08.620 --> 18:10.880
we can't be afraid
to give him a name that says

18:10.880 --> 18:12.420
"This is who I am."

18:12.420 --> 18:14.790
Oh, wow.

18:14.790 --> 18:18.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:18.880 --> 18:20.040
You're right.

18:20.040 --> 18:21.790
He shouldn't have to hide.

18:21.790 --> 18:22.960
And you know what?

18:22.960 --> 18:25.080
If he crosses paths
with somebody

18:25.080 --> 18:26.620
that judges him
because of his name...
 Mm-hmm.

18:26.620 --> 18:28.120
...then he doesn't want
that person in his life.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.000
Exactly.
 No.

18:30.000 --> 18:31.250
Oh! Foot. Foot.
 Ooh, ooh, ooh!

18:31.250 --> 18:32.790
Ooh, ooh, ooh!
 Foot. Right there.

18:32.790 --> 18:35.170
Whoa-ha-ha-oo!
 [ Laughs ]

18:35.170 --> 18:36.830
Oh, look at baby DeVonté.

18:36.830 --> 18:39.170
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

18:39.170 --> 18:43.040
If you want to name
our baby...
 Mm-hmm...

18:43.040 --> 18:45.250
after the third fiddle

18:45.250 --> 18:48.540
of the fifth most important
R&B band of the '90s --

18:48.540 --> 18:49.670
Fifth?!
 The fifth.

18:49.670 --> 18:51.290
Fifth?!
 Boyz II Men...

18:51.290 --> 18:52.960
Okay, don't let it
get you off track, Dre.
 ...Bell Biv DeVoe...

18:52.960 --> 18:56.250
I love the name.

18:58.500 --> 19:00.880
Then I love the name.

19:00.880 --> 19:02.830
Okay?
 Okay.

19:02.830 --> 19:03.920
[ Laughs ]

19:03.920 --> 19:05.670
So, DeVonté?
 DeVonté.

19:05.670 --> 19:06.420
Good.
 DeVonté.

19:06.420 --> 19:07.790
You know what?

19:07.790 --> 19:09.040
He's gonna be able to do
whatever he wants anyway,

19:09.040 --> 19:10.040
'cause he's our kid.

19:10.040 --> 19:12.250
He's gonna have my brain,

19:12.250 --> 19:15.290
and he's gonna have
your...[Stammers]

19:15.290 --> 19:17.000
My looks?
 Ye-- Uh...

19:17.000 --> 19:18.880
Your angry charm!
 You know what?

19:18.880 --> 19:20.540
I am charming
when I'm angry.

19:20.540 --> 19:21.830
The most.
 Ooh.

19:21.830 --> 19:23.170
All right.

19:23.170 --> 19:25.790
He will have
the middle name Matthew.

19:25.790 --> 19:27.380
Yes.
 Yes.

19:27.380 --> 19:30.420
Solid White-sounding
backup.
 Very important.

19:30.420 --> 19:32.880
Ahh! DeVonté Matthew,

19:32.880 --> 19:34.790
I think
you're my favorite!

19:34.790 --> 19:36.000
You are my favorite!

19:36.000 --> 19:36.920
Junior: Wow.

19:38.920 --> 19:41.500
I expect that from him,
but from you Mother?

19:41.500 --> 19:42.750
Stings.

19:42.750 --> 19:44.960
Zoey: [ Scoffs ]

19:49.210 --> 19:50.880
Oh, there you are.
I got the movie ready.

19:50.880 --> 19:52.290
Come on!
 Ohh, just got a text
from Shelly.

19:52.290 --> 19:53.170
We're going out.

19:53.170 --> 19:54.750
Huh?

19:54.750 --> 19:56.080
Sorry, kiddo.
Next time.

19:56.080 --> 19:56.920
Uh --

19:58.750 --> 20:01.120
[ Sighs ] Stupid Diane.

20:01.120 --> 20:03.460
This is what you get
for opening up your heart.

20:03.460 --> 20:05.670
Junior: One is vanilla,
one is french vanilla.

20:05.670 --> 20:07.500
I'm not sure
which is which.

20:07.500 --> 20:09.920
I bought them for a night
that will not materialize.

20:10.830 --> 20:11.830
Thanks.

20:11.830 --> 20:14.670
What are we watching?

20:14.670 --> 20:16.620
Trampoline accidents.
 All right.

20:16.620 --> 20:18.120
Girl: Come here, daddy!

20:18.120 --> 20:19.710
Watch! Watch this!

20:19.710 --> 20:20.500
[ Crash ]
 [ Screams ]

20:20.500 --> 20:21.500
Man: Ohh!

20:21.500 --> 20:22.250
Ohh.
 Ohh.
